    "Awake_Technique": {
      "text": "Sniffing position (like oral ET)\nPretreat with\nglycopyrrolate\n0.2mg or 0.04 mcg/kg and\nlido\n,\nhurricaine\n, or 4cc nebulized\nlidocaine\nfor 5 minutes\nAlso consider topical cocaine to the nares, typically 4% solution, for 2-3 minutes or intranasal\nphenylephrine\nProvide sedation with small doses of ketamine (10-20mg aliquots as needed) or midazolam\nTube size = 1.0 mm smaller\nListen with stethoscope  at end of tube (breath sounds become louder as tube approaches cords)\nWhen tube hits cords patient will cough, back up 1 or 2 cm.  wait for beginning of inspiration, as patient begins inspiration advance 3-4 cm (tube should be 22-26cm in women, 23-28cm in men)\nTips:\nOcclude other nostril to hear better\nCricoid pressure when advancing\nUse a small suction catheter as a seldinger guide\nPrecurve tube before insertion.",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "glycopyrrolate",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Glycopyrrolate"
        },
        {
          "text": "lido",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Lidocaine"
        },
        {
          "text": "hurricaine",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Benzocaine"
        },
        {
          "text": "lidocaine",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Lidocaine"
        },
        {
          "text": "phenylephrine",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Phenylephrine"
        }
      ]
    },
    "Sedated_Technique": {
      "text": "Prepare\nAfrin\nin 10 cc syringe, nasal trumpet, nasal tube (or smaller ETT) without stylet, DL blade, McGills/long curved Kellys\nAfrin in both nostrils\nNasal trumpet into right nostril to dilate nasal airway (R nostril = less bleeding, faster\n[1]\nInsert tube in a postero-inferior direction (may feel some crunching along ethmoid, so be careful along that surface)\nDL to visualize tube insertion past vocal cords\nMcGills or Kellys to grasp tube tip and facilitate passing tube",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "Afrin",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Afrin"
        }
      ]
    },
